SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S ENDOWMENT FUND (FUND) CONSISTS OF MULTIPLE INDIVIDUAL FUNDS ESTABLISHED FOR A VARIETY OF PURPOSES. THE FUND INCLUDES FUNDS DESIGNATED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS TO FUNCTION AS ENDOWMENTS. AS REQUIRED BY ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA, NET ASSETS ASSOCIATED WITH ENDOWMENT FUNDS, INCLUDING FUNDS DESIGNATED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS TO FUNCTION AS ENDOWMENTS, ARE CLASSIFIED AND REPORTED BASED ON THE EXISTENCE OR ABSENCE OF DONOR-IMPOSED RESTRICTIONS.

INCOME NOT RELATED TO THE FARM BUREAU'S TAX-EXEMPT PURPOSE MAY BE SUBJECT TO TAXATION AS UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME. GENERALLY ACCEPTED ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES IMPOSE A THRESHOLD FOR DETERMINING WHEN AN INCOME TAX BENEFIT CAN BE RECOGNIZED WITH REGARD TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS. THE FARM BUREAU HAS DETERMINED THAT THERE WAS NO IMPACT ON FINANCIAL REPORTING DUE TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS DURING THE YEAR ENDED OCTOBER 31, 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MEMBERS ALL PAY ANNUAL DUES. THERE ARE APPROXIMATELY 2,321 MEMBERS FOR THE YEAR ENDED 10/31/22.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH OF THE COUNTY BOARDS SELECTS DELEGATES FOR THE ANNUAL MEETING. THE DELEGATES ELECT THE SLATE OF OFFICERS, YOUNG FARMER & RANCHER COMMITTEE ELECTS THREE COUNTY CHAIRS AND THE STATE CHAIR TO SERVE ON THE STATE BOARD, THE WOMEN'S COMMITTEE ELECTS THREE COUNTY CHAIRS AND THE STATE CHAIR TO SERVE ON THE STATE BOARD, AND THE COUNTY BOARD ELECTS THEIR PRESIDENT TO SERVE ON THE STATE BOARD AND COUNTY DELEGATES ELECT THREE COUNTY REPRESENTATIVES TO SERVE ON THE STATE BOARD. ALL STATE BOARD MEMBERS SERVE UNTIL THEIR SUCCESSORS ARE DULY ELECTED AND QUALIFIED. ALL MEETINGS ARE OPEN TO THE MEMBERS, BUT ONLY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS VOTES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE DECISIONS OF THE GOVERNING BODY SUBJECT TO APPROVAL ARE DECISIONS ON BYLAWS, RESOLUTION, AND VOTING ELECTED OFFICERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PRESIDENT WILL PRESENT THE TAX RETURN TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE BEFORE FILING. AS TIME ALLOWS, THE RETURN WILL BE FORWARDED TO THE FULL BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL BOARD MEMBERS ARE TO REVIEW THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY UPON ACCEPTANCE BY THE BOARD. THE BOARD IS REQUIRED TO ANNUALLY DISCLOSE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AND SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST DISCLOSURE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE DETERMINES COMPENSATION FOR ALL STAFF AND OFFICERS. THE DETERMINATION IS MADE ANNUALLY AS PART OF THE BUDGET PROCESS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 18
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S FORM 990 IS AVAILABLE AT WWW.GUIDESTAR.ORG AND BY WRITTEN REQUEST TO THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE BY WRITTEN REQUEST TO THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR.
